    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough. but if originalism is \"subjective\" too, then isn't the \"living constitution\" approach basically just letting judges act like legislators? it seems like the living constitution side just picks whatever outcome they want and works backward to find a justification for it. doesn't that just undermine the whole point of having a written constitution in the first place?",
